  "name": "BPH - Medication Query (Alpha-blockers + 5-ARI)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find BPH patients via medication codes — alpha-blockers (tamsulosin, terazosin) and 5-alpha-reductase inhibitors (finasteride). Synthea distributes patients across these meds. Note: this query does NOT restrict to male/age-40+, so it would catch finasteride prescribed off-label (e.g., for androgenetic alopecia) — useful contrast to the dx test case.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed BPH medications, including alpha-blockers (tamsulosin, terazosin) and 5-alpha-reductase inhibitors (finasteride).",
